    "Cardiothoracic surgeon Bhaskara Rao Bollineni founded KIMS Hospitals in 2000 with a 200-bed hospital in his home town of Nellore in southern India.",
    "The company owns and operates 25 hospitals with a total of 8,300 beds across the states of Andhra Pradesh, Telangana, Karnataka, Maharashtra and Kerala.",
    "The older of his two sons, Abhinay, who's also a doctor, is chief executive while the younger son Adwik is has a board seat.",
    "Its flagship hospital in the southern city of Secundraabad has 1,000 beds.",
    "Bollineni has performed more than 30,000 surgeries over a career spanning nearly three decades."
